    %h2 Mission
    .align_left
      =image_tag "counter.jpg"
    The Food Co-Op's mission is to offer people an alternative place to shop for food and eat lunch. Since it exists on a college campus it attempts to allow students, faculty, staff, and off campus community members a space to coexist in a comfortable, non-judgmental environment. We strive to offer an alternative to the campus food monopoly Sodexo, one of the largest corporations in the world with a history of minimizing food quality and health benefits for workers. At the Co-Op we care deeply about the health of ourselves, our customers, our planet, and the animals who may sacrifice their lives for our nourishment. We do not push veganism or vegetarianism, in fact many Co-Op members are omnivores and we do sell meat at times purchased from local farms. The meat we sell is raised consciously with concern for the animal and the health of the consumer.
    <br><br>
    At the Co-Op the main mission, besides creating space, is to offer as much local and organic food as we possibly can. We do not stock anything in our store that is less than 70% organic and any produce or bulk items we carry we source from the most local distributors possible.  To read more about what the importance of local and organic food is, continue reading our "Know Your Food" section below.
    
